{
  "texts": [
    "Instead of being given a big pile of thousands of handcrafted features to consider, it used a deep neural network to automatically identify patterns and relationships that make particular moves attractive, the same way AlexNet had identified the visual textures and shapes that make a dod a dog and a cat a cat (Christian, 2020i).",
    "Again, hence an inspiration for AI-led architectural pattern-based design and analysis that later the section (4) will discuss.",
    "As implemented already in Deep Blue, focus on the process instead of the output/result provides another, even more important lesson for AI's deployment in AECO design.",
    "In October 2017, Google DeepMind brought this paradigm to a (so far) ultimate level by going through with the playing-against-itself strategy in AlpahGo Zero (AlphaGo, 2023b).",
    "AlphaGo combines advanced search trees with deep neural networks."
  ]
}